intef-exe (3:2.8.1) lucid; urgency=medium

  * Ignacio Gros
    - Snap version (no longer maintained): Access to NTFS partitions removed.
    - Properties tab: Custom HEAD and Footer. Allow TEXTAREA resize. (#666)
    - Example iDevice full revision. (#674)
    - Fixed: INTEF style. Accessibility issues and position problem. (#667)
    - Fixed: Block the DUA style so it can't be deleted. (#673)
    - Fixed: Wikipedia iDevice. CSS revision. (#665)
    - Fixed: DL lists. 'Show/Hide all' links removed and presentation revision. (#683)
    - Fixed: TinyMCE. Wrong font-family in tables. (#680)
    - Fixed: Avoid 'No clientHandleId in request' exception when reloading the main area. (#685)
    - Fixed: Hangman game. Untranslated string. (#689)

  * Pablo Amaya
    - AppImage source files for Debian package creation. Helped by Esteban Navas (@algodelinux)
    - Package building: Linux (deb, AppImage deb package). Helped by Esteban Navas (@algodelinux)
    - Fixed: Linux application name and icon. (#670)

  * APSL
    - Package building: Linux (rmp), Windows (ready2run, installer), macOS (dmg).
    - Fixed: IMS export. Missing files in imsmanifest.xml (#684)
    - Fixed: Windows / Mac. Application icon and name. (#678)
    
  * Manuel Narváez
    - Empty src attribute in games caused page reload (browser confirmation dialog on leaving page).
    
  * Regorxxx
    - Improve File Picker behavior to follow software standards.

 -- eXeLearning <admin@exelearning.net>  Fri, 19 May 2023 09:20:00 +0200

intef-exe (3:2.8) lucid; urgency=medium

  * Manuel Narváez
    - New Game: Complete (type or select).
      Design by Ana María Zamora and Francisco Javier Pulido.
    - New Game: Word Search (crossword puzzle).
      Design by Ana María Zamora.
    - New Game: Identify (guess a character or solution).
      Design by Ana María Zamora.
    - New Game: Memory Cards (flipping cards).
    - New Game: Math Operations (random basic operations).
      Design by Ana María Zamora.
      Previous code by Ignacio Gros.
    - New Game: Math Problems (random basic math problems).
      Design by Ana María Zamora.
      Previous code by Ignacio Gros.
    - New: Blackboard mode in all the games.
    - New: Accessibility warning in games that require it.
    - New: Instructions in all games.
    - New: You can use EducaMadrid's Mediateca (https://mediateca.educa.madrid.org/) videos and audios in the games. (#657)
    - New: Interactive Video iDevice is now SCORM compatible. Scores can be saved. (#650)
    - Multiple Choice Quiz iDevice usability revision.
    - Map iDevice: 404 errors fixed (#654) + Usability revision + New SVG icons + Effects in text slides.
    - Allow LaTeX code in more iDevices (Games and Interactive Video). MathJax will be loaded.
    - MathJax upgrade (from 2.7.1 to 3.2.2) and configuration update. Configuration options in common file. (#641)

  * Ignacio Gros
    - New Export preference: "Made with eXeLearning" footer link. (#638)
    - New Export preference: "Math content: Load MathJax in pages with LaTeX code". You can now type LaTeX code directly into the editor. (#639)
    - prettyPhoto (Lightbox): Link in new windows in IFRAME (SCORM and IMS only) + i18n. (#653)
    - "Add a Text iDevice" button in the main area. (#642)
    - Interactive Video iDevice: Cover image (poster) (#646) + Bigger player. (#652) + Multiple-choice score error. (#659)
    - TinyMCE Media plugin: New "Standard YouTube License" option (#624) + IFRAME attribution problems fixed (#634).
    - TinyMCE Math plugin: Allow inline formulas (LaTeX code). (#651)
    - TinyMCE syntax highlighting options: Error handling (wrong values in the "Line highlight" field).
    - TinyMCE Effects plugin: Presentation revision.
    - Licenses help links (Creative Commons) in some TinyMCE plugins and the Properties tab. (#649)
    - Responsive tables. Use "exe-table exe-table-responsive" or "exe-table-minimalist exe-table-responsive" CSS classes.
    - Presentation style: Presentation remotes (wireless presenters) compatibility. (#658)
    - Fixed: Accordion titles color in some styles (CEDEC and INTEF). (#660)
    
  * Pablo Amaya
    - New export option: "Export current page as SCORM". (#643)
    - Show the iDevice type name when editing, so you can know how to create similar contents. New added iDevices only. (#644)
    - Old "Add Previous/Next links within SCOs" export option removed. (#658)
    - Package building: Linux (AppImage deb package).
    
  * APSL
    - Mac problems fixed: Install styles from repository. (#656) + Download Classification Sources. (#569)
    - Fixed: User styles lost after installing a newer Snap package. For future upgrades only. (#661)
    - Fixed: Wikipedia iDevice failed in some languages. (#662)
    - Package building: Linux (deb, rmp, snap), Windows (ready2run, installer), macOS (dmg).

  * CEDEC
    - Rubric iDevice: Rubrics update + 6 new rubrics. (#645)

  * Antonio Monje
    - Games: Instructions (videos).

  * Dionisio Martínez Soler
    - Package building: Linux (AppImage).
    
  * Ricardo Nutz
    - Access to NTFS partitions with Snap version (only available in https://github.com/exelearning/iteexe/releases/tag/2.8).

  * Fran Macías
    - Package building: Portable versions (Linux, Windows).
    
  * Juan Rafael Fernández
    - String extraction process revision.
    - Translations coordination.  
    - PO/msgfmt and string errors fixed.

  * eXeLearning.net Translation Team
    - New complete Spanish translation, by Juan Rafael Fernández.
    - New complete Basque translation, by Joxemi Andonegi.
    - New complete Catalan translation, by Carles Ferrando Garcia.
    - New complete Galician translation, by Pablo Nimo.
    - New complete Valencian translation, by Ricardo Nutz.
    - New complete French translation, by Jesús Miguel Domínguez.
    - New complete Greek translation, by Yannis Kaskamanidis.
    - New complete Polish translation, by Waldemar Stoczkowski.
    - New complete Turkish translation, by Turkish Transifex team.
    - New Traditional Chinese translation, by Franklin Weng.

